# Intentional gaps in the migration sequence.
#
# Nova's migration runner globs *.sql in numeric-prefix order and runs each
# file idempotently — gaps are survivable. Numbers listed here were claimed
# by feature branches that never merged (or were skipped during early
# development). Listing them silences the migration-gap CI check.
#
# Adding new numbers here should require explicit review — the gap-check
# exists to surface ordering hazards across in-flight branches, and an
# entry here should always have a matching git-history note explaining
# WHY the gap is intentional.
#
# Format: one number per line; '#' comments and blank lines ignored.

042
043
# 084 was reserved for sec-006b-socket-proxy but that PR (#3) shipped a
# Docker socket-proxy change with no schema migration, so the number was
# never claimed. Intentional skip — confirmed via gh pr view 3.
084

# 088_engram_missing_columns.sql was deliberately deleted in commit
# 76a9012 ("delete migration 088 — it broke every fresh install for a
# dead feature") after the engram memory backend was shelved.
088

# 105-119 were reserved by the feature/autonomy-core lane (2026-07-09
# multi-session split; see PR #33) but never claimed — the branch merged
# with its schema changes numbered inside the existing sequence, and no
# file with these numbers ever existed in any ref (verified via
# `git log --all --diff-filter=A` on 2026-07-11). The sequence resumes
# at 120 (brain-ux lane).
105
